            <div class="container">
                <p>
                    I've had the pleasure of working with some amazing folks over the years. Most recently, my time has
                    been spent as a Software Engineer at Research Square. In the last several years there, I've made the
                    following contributions:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        I've converted a monolithic, decade-old code base from a disparate set of technologies (zend
                        framework 1, zf3, jQuery, assetify, grunt, and more) to a code base using a predictable feature
                        set (laminas, react, redux, and webpack).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        I've created internal tooling to aid in developer happiness and productivity, including a
                        [pull request bot](#) that posts notifications to Slack about open PRs, as well as a
                        [Retrospective](#) tool we use to aid in sprint planning & review.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        I've taken our companies Project management internal certification program, and have
                        successfully pushed a company-level [rock](https://www.eosworldwide.com/blog/is-that-really-a-rock)
                        from ideation to completion (along with countless smaller projects I've lead, championed,
                        and engineer through the years)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        I've worked to increase inclusivity in my workplace, including: Being an active participant in
                        Research Square's DEI (Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion) committee, leading a change in company
                        policy around the use of non-gender neutral terms in personnel surveys, and advocating for a
                        year of focusing our sprint names on [Kick-ass women](#) in history.
                    </li>
                </ul>
